<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-8229] Aggregate functions do not return expected values or metadata</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8229</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Aggregrate functions do not behave as expected on the following points:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If no row is selected the resultset returned is empty whereas in the case of aggregates it should returns some default values (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;SELECT count&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/star_yellow.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; ...&lt;/tt&gt; should return 0 if no row is returned).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The column name returned for &lt;tt&gt;max(a)&lt;/tt&gt; when a is an int is &lt;tt&gt;max(int -&amp;gt; int)&lt;/tt&gt; and should be &lt;tt&gt;max(a)&lt;/tt&gt; if no alias is used.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;When used with limit the value returned is not always the expected one. It sometimes include an extra row.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
