                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14191834" author="blerer" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 14:19:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This patch fix:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the problem that the column names returned for functions was wrong: &lt;tt&gt;max(int -&amp;gt; int)&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;max(a)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the problem that one row should be returned when aggregate functions are used even if the query was not returning any results. In which case the returned values are the initialization aggregate values (e.g. 0 for sum, null for max, null for avg, 0 for count)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the  problem that cqlsh was unable to handle count(a).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;The patch add also some unit test to check the proper handling of exclusive slice with compact storage&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14192517" author="thobbs" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 21:25:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only a couple of nits on the patch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are unused imports in SelectorFactories&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In &lt;tt&gt;assertColumnNames()&lt;/tt&gt;, calls to &lt;tt&gt;assertEquals()&lt;/tt&gt; should use the expected value as the first arg and the actual value second&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;I would name it &lt;tt&gt;getReturnType()&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;getOutputType()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14209676" author="blerer" created="Thu, 13 Nov 2014 12:20:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=thobbs&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;thobbs&quot;&gt;thobbs&lt;/a&gt; can you review the second patch?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14210063" author="thobbs" created="Thu, 13 Nov 2014 17:35:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I guess I missed the second patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1, committed as 4ff6e7d.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
